<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1499237-when-is-this-book-story-set-surely-not-in">When is this book/story set? Surely not in 1984? It reads like it is set in the times long past, with all the conventions described and the behaviour of ladies and gentlemen; was it before or slightly after the war?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1499237'><a id="like_count_community_question_1499237" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1499237?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F251665.Hotel_du_Lac">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1499237-when-is-this-book-story-set-surely-not-in">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1499237-when-is-this-book-story-set-surely-not-in">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/9644734-kristina"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/9644734-kristina">Kristina</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Based on Jennifer's fashion choices, I think this is around 1984 - knickerbockers were a thing for a short time. 1940s or 1950s would have had slacks <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Based on Jennifer's fashion choices, I think this is around 1984 - knickerbockers were a thing for a short time. 1940s or 1950s would have had slacks instead.<br /><br />I did keep picturing Monica and Mrs. Pusey in late 1920s fashion, despite thinking the setting was contemporary with the publication date.<br /><br />I think the "times long past" feel (I really like your phrase) has to do with the main character being rather out of touch with her own time and place which is probably meant to reflect her inner state.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

