<div id="review_2516937430" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2516937430" />
    <a title="Dan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10770371-dan"><img alt="Dan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1540580928p2/10770371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2516937430?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dan" href="/user/show/10770371-dan">Dan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10770371-dan?shelf=man-booker-prize">man-booker-prize</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2516937430" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16541415763556928812">Hotel du Lac by Anita Brookner won the Booker Prize in 1984.<br/><br/>A simple story with memorable characters and beautiful and efficient prose. Edith is a runaway bride and author who is on an extended vacation at the hotel. We meet a number of characters, most all are of privilege. We root for Edith throughout the novel. As the informed reader we come to know her introverted nature and we know the nature of men, especially those portrayed in this novel. <br/><br/>5 stars. This is an example of how to write an ex</span>
  <span id="freeText16541415763556928812" style="display:none">Hotel du Lac by Anita Brookner won the Booker Prize in 1984.<br /><br />A simple story with memorable characters and beautiful and efficient prose. Edith is a runaway bride and author who is on an extended vacation at the hotel. We meet a number of characters, most all are of privilege. We root for Edith throughout the novel. As the informed reader we come to know her introverted nature and we know the nature of men, especially those portrayed in this novel. <br /><br />5 stars. This is an example of how to write an excellent novel without relying on any seismic events. Hotel du Lac reminded me of Bel Canto by Ann Patchett and Magic Mountain by Thomas Mann, both of which I love.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16541415763556928812" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


